Distribution.
Corallium johnsoni
is known from the northeast Atlantic Ocean (
Watling & Auster 2005
; Watling et al . 2011 ), although there is a record (name in species list) from northeastern Canada (
Fuller et al . 2008
;
NAFO 2008
) that should be verified. The holotype was harvested off Madeira at an unknown depth (
Gray 1860
;
Johnson 1899
), and the species was later reported from the Azores , Portugal , and off Ireland between 919–1241 m depth (
Stephens 1909
;
Thomson 1927
;
Carpine & Grasshoff 1985
;
Sampaio et al . 2009
).
